Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1%unit}. Zest and quarter @Lime{1%unit}. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @Green Bell Pepper{1%unit}. Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1%unit}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces until you have 4 cups. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1%unit}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine ¼ of the onion, juice from half the lime, ½ tsp @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, 1 TBSP water, and @Salt{}. Stir until sugar and salt are mostly dissolved. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and 2 TBSP water.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add remaining onion; season with half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

While veggies cook, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Season all over with remaining Southwest Spice, salt, and pepper.

Once onion is slightly tender, push veggies to one side of pan. Add another drizzle of oil to empty side, then add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove pan from heat.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest.

In a second #small bowl{}, whisk together @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, @Buttermilk Ranch Dressing{1.5%ounce}, a squeeze of lime juice, ¼ tsp @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, a pinch of @Chipotle Powder{1%teaspoon} to taste, and a pinch of lime zest to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together chopped lettuce, tomato, and half the dressing (save the rest for serving). Season with a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise. (Alternatively, dice into 1-inch pieces.)

Divide salad between plates or #large bowls{}; top with fajita veggies, chicken, and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Drizzle with remaining dressing to taste. Crush @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce} and garnish with as many crushed tortilla chips as you like.

> TIP: Drizzle bowls with hot sauce from your pantry if you want a spicy kick!